Norilsk Gains as Citigroup Says Share Drop Is Overdone

-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 
2011-08-12T15:20:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-12/norilsk-gains-as-citigroup-says-share-drop-is-overdone-1-.html
OAO GMK Norilsk Nickel gained for
the second day this week as Citigroup Inc. said Russia’s largest
mining company is a “bounce-back candidate” and cheap compared
with foreign peers.  The shares climbed 4 percent to 6,737 rubles by the 6:45
p.m. close  in Moscow, paring their weekly loss to 4.5 percent.  The stock currently offers a 20 percent discount based on
earnings multiples to miners in the U.K., Mikhail Seleznev and
Daniel Yakub at Citigroup wrote in an e-mailed note today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at 
 gserkin@bloomberg.net  